HEADWORD: Trachymedusae
<hw>Tra`chy*me*du"sae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr.Gr. <?/ rough + <ets>medusa</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of acalephs in which the development
is direct from the eggs, without a hydroid stage. Some of the species
are parasitic on other medusae.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trachyspermous</ent>⟦br⟧
